# Preecursor — build-time environment variables.
# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are inlined
# into the client bundle at build time and are therefore public by design.

# Google Analytics 4 measurement id, e.g. G-XXXXXXXXXX.
# Read by components/Analytics.tsx. Leave empty to disable analytics entirely
# (the component renders nothing). For production, set this as a repository
# VARIABLE named NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID (GitHub → Settings → Secrets and variables →
# Actions → Variables) — the deploy workflow passes it into the build. It is a
# public id, not a secret, so a Variable (not a Secret) is the correct home.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=
